  "local_port": 34292,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Technical product manager questions?",
  "response": "Absolutely! Here are some common questions that might be asked during an interview for a Technical Product Manager position:\n\n### General Questions\n1. **Tell me about yourself and your background.**\n2. **How did you get into product management?**\n3. **Why do you want to work as a Technical Product Manager?**\n4. **What attracts you to our company/product?**\n5. **How do you stay updated with the latest technology trends?**\n6. **What do you think is the most important skill for a Technical Product Manager to have?**\n\n### Product Management Questions\n1. **Walk me through your product management process.**\n2. **How do you prioritize features and tasks?**\n3. **Can you describe a time when you managed a product from concept to launch?**\n4. **How do you handle feedback from customers?**\n5. **What metrics do you track to measure product success?**\n6. **Can you give an example of a successful product you managed? What made it successful?**\n\n### Technical Understanding Questions\n1. **Explain a technical concept to me as if I were a non-technical stakeholder.**\n2. **How do you work with engineering teams to define product requirements?**\n3. **Describe a time when you had to make a technical decision. How did you approach it?**\n4. **How do you ensure that the development team understands the product requirements clearly?**\n5. **What is your approach to handling technical debt?**\n\n### Collaboration and Communication Questions\n1. **How do you ensure effective communication between cross-functional teams?**\n2. **How do you handle disagreements between engineering and product management?**\n3. **Can you describe a time when collaboration led to a better product outcome?**\n4. **How do you present product updates to stakeholders?**\n5. **What tools or methods do you use to maintain documentation and track progress?**\n\n### Behavioral Questions\n1. **Tell me about a challenging project you've worked on and how you overcame the challenges.**\n2. **Describe a situation where you had to handle multiple high-priority tasks simultaneously.**\n3. **How do you handle failure or setbacks on a project?**\n\n### Scenario-Based Questions\n1. **Imagine you're given a vague product idea. How would you proceed?**\n2. **A stakeholder disagrees with the prioritization of a feature. How do you handle it?**\n3. **You're launching a new product and discover a critical bug at the last minute. What do you do?**\n4. **How would you approach enhancing a product that's underperforming in the market?**\n\nThese questions are designed to assess a candidate's technical understanding, product management skills, and ability to collaborate and communicate effectively. Good luck with your interview!",
